 This Photographer Snuck Into the Wrecked Cruise Ship Costa Concordia 
 
 
 
 Jun 28, 2017 
 
 
 Michael Zhang 
 
 
 
 
 2259 
 Shares 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 0 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 On January 13th, 2012, the giant Italian cruise ship Costa Concordia capsized and sank off Isola del Giglio, Tuscany, after running into an underwater rock, claiming 32 lives. In August 2014, in the midst of the salvaging operation, photographer  Jonathan Danko Kielkowski  secretly snuck onto the shi